David/Cindy, 

I have arranged for Dick Jeanrette, who is an industrial psychologist 
specializing in employment matters, to assist us in the performance 
evaluation process.  Dick has worked for years with Exxon, which has a 
process that sounds similar to ours, and has many ideas regarding the 
process.  The Exxon process has been challenged in court, and Dick has 
testified about its process; the cases have been in favor of the company.  
Thus, I believe his experience and insight will help us in our performance 
management process.

I will be arranging a meeting with Dick in the next two weeks.  Besides the 
persons identified in this email, who should attend?  You had mentioned Steve 
Kean.  Should he be involved as well?  (FYI, he worked with Dick on Project 
One).

Let me know if you have any questions.

Michelle




