Michelle,

I had a voicemail from Cindy and Steve Kean relating to the change of wording 
on the Satisfactory and Needs Improvement descriptors for this mid-year 
review. Concern surrounds the apparent toughening of Satisf in particular and 
a belief that this makes distributing names into bottom 2 categories harder.

I recall we changed wording due to some concerns you had expressed. Perhaps 
you can restate them here for everyone.

However, regardless of above I remain of opinion that descriptors and labels 
are proving a distraction from what should be a more relative process. 
Perhaps the main message here is to convey something that helps us put these 
descriptors in the context of a guide only (starting point or indicative 
illustration) rather than absolute scale. 

Bottom-line it is rather difficult to see how we could change any of this for 
the mid year.

David
















